docs.snippet: Mr. Moonves had already been negotiating his departure before a report on Sunday detailed new sexual harassment allegations against him.
docs.lead_paragraph: Leslie Moonves, the longtime chief executive of the CBS Corporation, stepped down on Sunday night from the company he led for 15 years. His fall from Hollywood’s highest echelon was all but sealed after the publication earlier in the day of new sexual harassment allegations against him.

headline.main: CBS Chief Executive Les Moonves Steps Down After Sexual Harassment Claims
headline.print_headline: CBS Chief Is Out As More Women Cite Misconduct
